
                                            ANC Treasurer-General Zweli Mkhize says he’s confident there will be no disruptions at the upcoming elective conference.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - African National Congress (ANC) Treasurer-General Zweli Mkhize says he’s confident there will be no disruptions at the upcoming elective conference. Mkhize told Eyewitness News the organisation is working to resolve branch disputes and appeals where there has either been gatekeeping or membership fraud. Mkhize says they are prepared to resolve all problems ahead of the elective conference. “Teams have been sent to provinces to try and resolve disputes and all the logistical preparations are in place for the conference to take place. We’ll do everything to make sure that this conference doesn’t get disturbed.” WATCH: ANC media briefing on readiness for national conference 